---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';

const title = "ADA Parking Lot Striping Springfield MO | Accessible Compliance Striping";
const description = "ADA-compliant parking lot striping in Springfield MO. We connect you with certified contractors who specialize in accessible stall layout, van accessible spaces, access aisles, and full compliance documentation for Greene County commercial properties.";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "name": "Springfield Lot Striping",
  "description": "We connect property managers and facility owners with certified commercial parking lot striping contractors.",
  "serviceType": "Commercial Parking Lot Striping"
};

---

<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <Header />
  
  <div class="pt-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-primary-dark">ADA Parking Lot Striping in Springfield, Missouri</h1>
      <div class="text-brand-yellow text-xl mt-2">Compliance-Focused • Documented • Local</div>
      
      <img src="/images/xai_grok-imagine-image_20260623_180927_63d294da.jpg" alt="ADA compliant parking lot striping Springfield Missouri" class="my-12 rounded-2xl shadow-xl w-full" />
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-concrete leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl">We connect property managers and facility owners in Springfield with top-rated, fully certified contractors who specialize in ADA-compliant parking lot striping. Springfield has a growing number of medical offices, retail centers, apartment communities, and mixed-use properties that must meet current federal accessibility standards.</p>
        
        <p>Whether you manage a medical building on East Sunshine, a retail center near Glenstone, or a multi-tenant property along the James River corridor, proper ADA striping is no longer optional. Inspectors, insurance companies, and tenants expect clear, correctly sized accessible stalls, proper access aisles, and accurate signage.</p>

        <h2>Why Springfield Properties Need Specialized ADA Striping</h2>
        <p>Springfield commercial lots often face unique challenges. Many older properties were striped before current ADA standards were enforced. Others have been repaved or reconfigured multiple times, leaving stall counts, access aisles, and accessible routes out of compliance. High tenant turnover and frequent re-leasing also mean layouts that worked five years ago may no longer meet requirements.</p>
        
        <p>We match you with contractors who understand how to read existing conditions, identify non-compliant elements, and deliver a clean, documented striping plan that satisfies both the letter and the spirit of ADA guidelines.</p>

        <h2>Services Included in ADA Striping Projects</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Correctly sized accessible stalls and van-accessible spaces</li>
          <li>Proper access aisle placement and dimensions</li>
          <li>Clear, high-visibility access aisle striping and curb painting</li>
          <li>ADA-compliant directional arrows and accessible route markings</li>
          <li>Before-and-after photographic documentation</li>
          <li>Measurement records suitable for inspections and insurance</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Common ADA Issues We See in Springfield</h2>
        <p>Many Springfield lots have faded or incorrectly placed accessible stalls. Some properties lack the required number of accessible spaces relative to total stall count. Others have access aisles that are too narrow or improperly located. These issues create both compliance risk and potential liability.</p>
        
        <p>Our network of contractors focuses on getting these details right the first time, with clear documentation that protects property owners and managers.</p>

        <div class="bg-surface p-10 rounded-3xl my-12">
          <p class="italic">"We needed to bring three medical office buildings into ADA compliance before a scheduled inspection. The work was completed over two nights with full documentation. No issues during the inspection."</p>
          <p class="mt-6 font-semibold">— Property Manager, Springfield Medical Plaza</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Ready to Bring Your Springfield Lot Into Compliance?</h2>
        <p>If your parking lot needs updated ADA striping, proper documentation, or a full compliance review, we connect you with experienced local contractors who specialize in this work.</p>
        
        <p class="text-center my-12">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary text-xl px-14 py-6 inline-block">Request Your Free ADA Striping Assessment →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>